text: Phryneta hecphora is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by James Thomson in 1857. It is known from Mozambique and Democratic Republic of the Congo.BioLib.cz - Phryneta hecphora. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Lamiinae Category:Beetles described in 1857
